ADOPTION OF SFAS NO. 123R

WE

EARLY ADOPTED THE PROVISIONS OF SFAS NO. 123R AS OF JANUARY 1, 2005 USING THE MODIFIED PROSPECTIVE METHOD. PRIOR TO THE ADOPTION OF SFAS NO. 123R, WE AMORTIZED COMPENSATION COST FOR SHARE-BASED AWARDS OVER THE STATED VESTING PERIOD

FOR RETIREMENT ELIGIBLE EMPLOYEES AND, IF AN EMPLOYEE RETIRED BEFORE THE END OF THE VESTING PERIOD, WE RECOGNIZED ANY REMAINING UNRECOGNIZED COMPENSATION COST AT THE DATE OF RETIREMENT. HAD WE APPLIED THE NON-SUBSTANTIVE VESTING APPROACH TO AWARDS

GRANTED PRIOR TO 2005, COMPENSATION EXPENSE WOULD HAVE BEEN $0, $6 AND $50 LOWER FOR THE YEARS ENDED DECEMBER 31, 2008, 2007 AND 2006.

PERFORMANCE SHARES

PERFORMANCE SHARES ARE STOCK UNITS THAT ARE CONVERTIBLE TO COMMON STOCK, ON A ONE-TO-ONE BASIS, CONTINGENT UPON STOCK PRICE PERFORMANCE. IF, AT ANY TIME UP TO

FIVE YEARS AFTER AWARD, THE STOCK PRICE REACHES AND MAINTAINS FOR TWENTY CONSECUTIVE DAYS A PRICE EQUAL TO STATED PRICE GROWTH TARGETS, A STATED PERCENTAGE (UP TO 125%) OF THE PERFORMANCE SHARES AWARDED ARE VESTED AND CONVERTIBLE TO COMMON STOCK.

